\begin_layout Standard
A series of approximations and a fully self-consistent hybrid approach combining
 a QM solute description with 3D RISM for the solvent medium reveals that,
 for neutral solutes, the accuracy of the calculated solvation free energies
 is mainly determined by the asymptotic error of the cavity formation energies.
 Significantly better agreement with experimental results could be obtained
 by applying the “partial molar volume” (PMV) correction, as also reported
